title: Leicester City 2-0 Chelsea FC - Does This Spell THE END Of Frank Lampard?
tags: Leicester City 2-0 Chelsea FC|chelsea news|latest chelsea news|chelsea f.c.|chelsea highlights|chelsea FC highlights|chelsea FC daily|chelsea football club|chelsea fc news|frank lampard press conference|football therapy|chelsea news live|chelsea news today|chelsea transfer news today live update|chelsea 2020/21|chelsea vs leicester city|leicester city vs chelsea highlights|leicester city vs chelsea goals|james maddison|wilfred ndidi|frank lampard sacked
description: Leicester City 2-0 Chelsea FC - Does This Spell THE END Of Frank Lampard?Leicester moved to the top of the Premier League after sweeping aside Chelsea with a comfortable 2-0 victory at the King Power Stadium.Brendan Rodgers' side got off to the perfect start when Wilfred Ndidi's strike gave them the lead in the sixth minute. Chelsea thought they had been given a route back into the game when referee Craig Pawson adjudged Jonny Evans to have fouled Christian Pulisic inside the penalty area.
